beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: another great creation of "mixing it up"   along with Extremely Rare..... dark amber in color, huge boozy smell of Brandy and Cognac  , Thick bodied , notes of vanilla and hazelnut stick to youre tongue long after tasting ....not to Overwhelming for a 15%er , great to enjoy now but will most Def Age well.    a Beer i must say even the Pope would Choose..!   Cheers

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: release at brewery . pours deep black , mild Thick tan head, huge aromas of coffee , Taste a Great Complexity of coffee beans , small choco taste. i absolutely dislike Black coffee . but i wish i had a cup of this every morning...
beer_name: Lost Abbey Box Set: Track #10 (Bat out of Hell)

review_blob: ....bought a bottle at The Bruery ....  deep murky brownish black...huge nose of smoke and wood....not overdone...Great beer with Ribs,   very intense beer so prepare to share .... i hate to Compare (but alot like Firestone annv  w/ added smoke )   overall another must have
beer_name: The Bruery Smoking Wood - Rye Barrel

review_blob: ...im purposely overrating the crap outta this because i think its wonderful....you shmucks need to EXPAND your mind....what did you expect from an extremely off the wall bottle?  and type of beer style?,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,    My first try was a bottle given to me At my wedding (thanks ERIC W)   it was  weird...but every sip it grew and grew on me... huge smell of Maple and bacon...like a country breakfast in your mouth...this is THE KING OF BREAKFAST BEERS...  not for afternoon consumption  and certainly not to be opened with any other beer...Breakfast only,  in small quantities.....Great job ROGUE....Yea its FU%KIN Weird but boy you gotta try it..!
beer_name: Rogue Voodoo Doughnut Bacon Maple Ale

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: ..had it at the release and various tastings...pours deep murky choco brown...slight brown head, vanilla ,bourbon and oak kick your cheeks...soo tasty ...very well priced considering it hold up to the best of them....another one you gotta try..!
beer_name: Port Brewing Santas Little Helper - Bourbon Barrel

review_blob: ....ok here we go....this is without a doubt a must for sour addicts ....did i mention its freakin sour?  pours a gorgeous yellow  no real head, outrageous nose..people mistake its HUGE citrus appeal ..for a vinegar smell....(grind up lemon rine and snort it...just the same)...complex taste of citrus sour...not for the vinegar lover..   another great beer..!
beer_name: The Bruery Provisions Series: Mother Funker

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: ...Tasted @ lost abbey Release...(many bottles)......Pours very deep Red in color slight white "Head".....slight sour smell,  hate to compare it to other beers...but  very similar to Consecration, mixed with Duchess.....Not too sour...and not over kill in Vinegar ...Cuvee w/ currant = great job guys...another killer track!
beer_name: Lost Abbey Box Set: Track #9 (Knockin on Heavens Door)

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: ...this beer is by far not what youd expect......your mind thinks judgement day on crack...your pallet says coconut ....its a very unique beer that shows Barrels Work magic!
beer_name: Lost Abbey Box Set: Track #8 (Number of the Beast)
